  <slide>
    <title>A11yFirst Project Goals</title>
    <contents>
      <ul>
        <li class="more">Accessible authoring versus accessibility remediation.</li>
        <li class="more">Support accessibility as content is created.</li>
        <li class="more">Teach authors about accessibility.</li>
      </ul>
    </contents>
  </slide>


  <slide>
    <title>Current User Thinking of WYSISWYG</title>
    <contents>
      <ol>
        <li class="more">What does the page look like.</li>
        <li class="more">HTML markup is about styling than structure.</li>
        <li class="more">Not aware of accessibility requirements.</li>
        <li class="more">Not aware of accessibility issues.</li>
        <li class="more">Accessibility takes more time and is hard (e.g. remidation).</li>
      </ol>
    </contents>
  </slide>

  <slide>
    <title>Changing User Thinking About Accessibiliy</title>
    <contents>
      <ol>
        <li class="more">Accessibility is important to the organization.</li>
        <li class="more">Accessibility is part of their responsibilities.</li>
        <li class="more">How to use HTML semantics of headings, lists and other structural markup.</li>
        <li class="more">Accessibility of link text.</li>
        <li class="more">Providing descriptions of images.</li>
        <li class="more">Accessibility is part of the authoring process.</li>
      </ol>
    </contents>
  </slide>

